### Fix 1 — `src/components/ui/Navigation/Navigation.module.scss`

The three-property identity lock needs to be complete. `.logo` gets `min-width: max-content` to close the flex-base loophole. `.links` gets an explicit `flex: 1 1 0` so it *owns* all the squeeze instead of fighting the logo for it. The existing `white-space: nowrap` on `.logoText` stays.

```scss
@use '../../../styles' as *;

.nav {
  position: sticky;
  top: 0;
  z-index: var(--portfolio-z-sticky);
  background-color: var(--portfolio-surface-terra-subtle);
  box-shadow: 0 4px 12px -4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);

  &::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    height: 10px;
    transform: translateY(100%);
    backdrop-filter: blur(3px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(3px);
    mask-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2), transparent);
    -webkit-mask-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2), transparent);
    pointer-events: none;
  }
}

.navInner {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  // Never allow the nav row to wrap. The identity lock (logo + name) is
  // non-negotiable — flex-wrap: nowrap is the outer fence; .logo's own
  // properties are the inner fence (see AP-066).
  flex-wrap: nowrap;
  max-width: $elan-container-wide;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: var(--portfolio-spacer-1-5x) var(--portfolio-spacer-2x);

  @media #{$elan-mq-sm} {
    padding: var(--portfolio-spacer-1-5x) var(--portfolio-spacer-4x);
  }
}

.logo {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: $portfolio-spacer-0-5x;
  text-decoration: none;

  // ─── Identity lock (AP-066) ────────────────────────────────────────────────
  // Three properties work in concert. Any single one is insufficient:
  //   1. flex-shrink: 0        — prevents the logo from shrinking below its
  //                              flex base size under space pressure.
  //   2. min-width: max-content — closes the flex-base loophole: forces the
  //                              flex base to resolve to the full intrinsic
  //                              content width, so the browser cannot choose a
  //                              narrower base that allows internal wrapping.
  //   3. white-space: nowrap   — on .logoText — prevents the text node itself
  //                              from breaking regardless of computed width.
  // Together: the logo NEVER wraps or compresses at any viewport width.
  // .links absorbs all squeeze via flex: 1 1 0; .tagline wraps within it.
  // ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  flex-shrink: 0;
  min-width: max-content;
  @include transition-fast;

  &:hover {
    .logoMark {
      background-color: var(--portfolio-text-neutral-max);
    }

    .logoText {
      color: var(--portfolio-text-neutral-max);
    }
  }
}

.logoMark {
  display: inline-block;
  height: calc($portfolio-type-2xl * 1.2);
  aspect-ratio: 1;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  background-color: $portfolio-accent-60;
  mask-image: url('/images/yg-logo.svg');
  mask-size: contain;
  mask-repeat: no-repeat;
  @include transition-fast;
}

.logoText {
  font-family: $portfolio-font-serif;
  font-size: $portfolio-type-2xl;
  font-weight: $portfolio-weight-regular;
  line-height: $portfolio-leading-snug;
  color: $portfolio-accent-60;
  letter-spacing: $portfolio-tracking-tight;
  // Part of the three-property identity lock — see .logo comment above.
  white-space: nowrap;
  @include transition-fast;
}

.links {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--portfolio-spacer-3x);

  // .links is the designated squeeze absorber. flex: 1 1 0 means it:
  //   • grows to fill any leftover space (flex-grow: 1)
  //   • shrinks when the nav is squeezed (flex-shrink: 1)
  //   • starts from zero base width (flex-basis: 0) so min-width governs
  // min-width: 0 overrides the default `min-width: auto` that would otherwise
  // prevent shrinking below content size — allowing children to wrap freely.
  flex: 1 1 0;
  min-width: 0;
  justify-content: flex-end;
}

.link {
  font-family: var(--portfolio-font-sans);
  font-size: var(--portfolio-type-sm);
  font-weight: var(--portfolio-weight-regular);
  color: var(--portfolio-text-secondary);
  text-decoration: none;
  @include transition-fast;

  &:hover {
    color: var(--portfolio-text-primary);
  }
}

.linkActive {
  color: var(--portfolio-text-primary);
  font-weight: var(--portfolio-weight-medium);
}

.tagline {
  @include body-sm;
  color: var(--portfolio-text-secondary);

  // The tagline is the designated yield surface of the nav. It absorbs squeeze
  // by wrapping to a second line (max 2 lines). It never compromises the logo.
  // Permitted to wrap — that is the design intent.
  min-width: 0;
  text-align: right;
  display: -webkit-box;
  -webkit-box-orient: vertical;
  -webkit-line-clamp: 2;
  line-clamp: 2;
  overflow: hidden;
}
```

