### Fix 2 — `docs/design-anti-patterns.md` — Amend AP-066

Locate the existing AP-066 block (in the **Navigation & Menus** section) and replace it with the sharpened version that codifies the three-property rule and names the yield-surface doctrine:

```markdown
<a id="ap-066"></a>
## AP-066: Unconstrained Flex Compression Breaking Identity Text

**Status: ACTIVE**
**Last amended:** 2026-04-27 (FB-146 — three-property identity lock codified;
yield-surface doctrine added.)

**Trigger:** A flex nav row where the logo/brand name is protected by only
`flex-shrink: 0` or only `white-space: nowrap`, but not both together with
`min-width: max-content` — causing the identity text to wrap at narrow viewports.

**Why it's wrong:** Any single property is insufficient:
- `flex-shrink: 0` alone prevents shrinking below the flex *base* size, but
  the browser resolves `flex-basis: auto` to a width that can still be narrower
  than the text's intrinsic width under certain box-model calculations, allowing
  internal wrapping.
- `white-space: nowrap` on the text node alone doesn't set the flex item's
  minimum occupied width — the flex algorithm can still assign the container a
  width that forces a wrap before the nowrap kicks in.
- `min-width: max-content` alone locks the minimum width but won't prevent
  flex-shrink from compressing the item if `flex-shrink` is non-zero.

All three properties must be present on the logo flex item for the guarantee to
hold at every viewport width.

**The two-tier contract:**
Every nav row has exactly two tiers:
1. **Identity tier** (logo + name) — absolutely rigid. Never wraps, never
   shrinks, never compromises. Enforced with the three-property lock below.
2. **Yield tier** (tagline, nav links) — the designated absorber. Wraps freely
   up to a capped number of lines. `flex: 1 1 0` + `min-width: 0` on the
   containing flex child makes this explicit.

**Correct alternative — three-property identity lock:**
```scss
// On the logo flex item:
.logo {
  flex-shrink: 0;          // never compress below flex base
  min-width: max-content;  // floor the flex base at intrinsic content width
}

// On the logo text node:
.logoText {
  white-space: nowrap;     // prevent internal line breaks regardless of width
}

// On the nav row:
.navInner {
  flex-wrap: nowrap;       // outer fence — the row itself never wraps
}

// On the yield-tier container:
.links {
  flex: 1 1 0;             // explicitly owns all squeeze
  min-width: 0;            // permits shrinking below content width
}
```

**Identity items that must NEVER wrap:** Logo mark, logo text ("Yilan Gao"),
any single-word or compound identity label that constitutes a proper name,
title, or brand identifier in a nav context.

**Items that MAY wrap (yield tier):** Taglines, role descriptors, nav link
lists on narrow viewports, any copy that is descriptive rather than
identifying.

**See:** FB-146.
```

